comment:
* IMS Voice configs. This groups the configs required for IMS Voice - VoNR/VoLTE * *

Reference: IR.92

variables.name: KEY_PREFIX
variables.comment: Prefix of all imsvoice.KEY_* constants.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_ROAMING_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether VoLTE should be available when on * roaming network. * *

If {@code false}: hard disabled. * If {@code true}: then depends on availability, etc.

variables.name: KEY_INCLUDE_CALLER_ID_SERVICE_CODES_IN_SIP_INVITE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether to send vertical caller id service codes * (*67 and *82) in the dialed string in the SIP:INVITE. * *

If {@code true}, vertical caller id service codes *67 and *82 * will be sent in the dialed string in the SIP:INVITE. * If {@code false}, *67 and *82 will be removed.

variables.name: KEY_MULTIENDPOINT_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment: * Flag indicating whether Multi-end point setting is enabled or not.

variables.name: KEY_SESSION_TIMER_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether Supported header field with the option tag * 'timer' is enabled or not. * *

If {@code true}, session timer support is available.{@code false} otherwise. * * Reference: RFC 4028 Section 3

variables.name: KEY_SESSION_EXPIRES_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Session-expires header field expressed in seconds as per * RFC 4028 Section 3. * *

This establishes the upper bound for the session refresh interval.

variables.name: KEY_MINIMUM_SESSION_EXPIRES_TIMER_SEC_INT
variables.comment:
* Indicates the minimum value for the session interval in seconds. * Represented as min-SE header field as per RFC 4028 Section 3. * *

This establishes the lower bound for the session refresh interval.

variables.name: SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UNKNOWN
variables.comment:
* Session Refresher entity is unknown. This means UE does not include the
         * "refresher" parameter in the Session-Expires header field of
         * the SIP INVITE request.

variables.name: SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UAC
variables.comment:
* Session Refresher entity is User Agent Client (UAC). * *

Type of "refresher" parameter in the Session-Expires header field * of the SIP INVITE request is UAC.

variables.name: SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UAS
variables.comment:
* Session Refresher entity is User Agent Server (UAS). * *

Type of "refresher" parameter in the Session-Expires header field * of the SIP INVITE request is UAS.

variables.name: KEY_SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Session Refresher entity as per RFC 4028 and IR.92 Section 2.2.8. * *

This determines, * a) whether to include the "refresher" parameter * b) Type of refresher" parameter * in the Session-Expires header field of the SIP INVITE request. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UNKNOWN}, * {@link #SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UAC}, * {@link #SESSION_REFRESHER_TYPE_UAS}

variables.name: SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_HEADER
variables.comment: * Session privacy type is HEADER as per RFC 3323 Section 4.2.

variables.name: SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_NONE
variables.comment: * Session privacy type is NONE as per RFC 3323 Section 4.2.

variables.name: SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_ID
variables.comment: * Session privacy type is ID as per RFC 3325 Section 9.3.

variables.name: KEY_SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Specify the session privacy type. * *

Reference: RFC 3323 Section 4.2, RFC 3325 Section 9.3. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_HEADER}, * {@link #SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_NONE}, * {@link #SESSION_PRIVACY_TYPE_ID}

variables.name: KEY_PRACK_SUPPORTED_FOR_18X_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether PRACK must be enabled for all 18x messages. * *

If {@code false}, only 18x responses with SDP are sent reliably. * If {@code true}, SIP 18x responses (other than SIP 183 response) * are sent reliably.

variables.name: CONFERENCE_SUBSCRIBE_TYPE_IN_DIALOG
variables.comment:
* The SIP SUBSCRIBE to conference state events is sent in the * SIP INVITE dialog between the UE and the conference server. * *

Reference: IR.92 Section 2.3.3.

variables.name: CONFERENCE_SUBSCRIBE_TYPE_OUT_OF_DIALOG
variables.comment:
* The SIP SUBSCRIBE to conference state events is sent out of * the SIP INVITE dialog between the UE and the conference server. * *

Reference: IR.92 Section 2.3.3.

variables.name: KEY_CONFERENCE_SUBSCRIBE_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* This is used to specify whether the SIP SUBSCRIBE to conference state events, * is sent in or out of the SIP INVITE dialog between the UE and the * conference server. * *

Reference: IR.92 Section 2.3.3. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #CONFERENCE_SUBSCRIBE_TYPE_IN_DIALOG}, * {@link #CONFERENCE_SUBSCRIBE_TYPE_OUT_OF_DIALOG} * * An empty array indicates SUBSCRIBE to conference event package * is not required.

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_QOS_PRECONDITION_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether QoS preconditions are supported during call setup. * *

If {@code true}: QoS Preconditions are supported during call setup and * 'precondition' tag is included in the SIP INVITE header and precondition * parameters are sent in SDP as required. *

If {@code false}: QoS Preconditions are not supported during call setup. * *

Reference: 3GPP TS 24.229

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_ON_DEFAULT_BEARER_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether voice is allowed on default bearer. * *

If {@code true}: voice packets can be sent on default bearer. {@code false} otherwise.

variables.name: KEY_DEDICATED_BEARER_WAIT_TIMER_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the dedicated bearer wait time during call establishment. * *

If dedicated bearer is not established within this time and if * {@link #KEY_VOICE_ON_DEFAULT_BEARER_SUPPORTED_BOOL} is false, then call setup would fail. *

If dedicated bearer is not established within this time and if * {@link #KEY_VOICE_ON_DEFAULT_BEARER_SUPPORTED_BOOL} is true, then the media is allowed * on default bearer.

variables.name: BASIC_SRVCC_SUPPORT
variables.comment:
* Indicates support for basic SRVCC, typically 1 active call
         * as detailed in IR.92 Section A.3.

variables.name: ALERTING_SRVCC_SUPPORT
variables.comment:
* SRVCC access transfer for calls in alerting phase as per 3GPP 24.237
         * and IR.64 Section 4.4.
         * Media feature tag used: g.3gpp.srvcc-alerting.

variables.name: PREALERTING_SRVCC_SUPPORT
variables.comment:
* SRVCC access transfer for calls in pre-alerting phase as per 3GPP 24.237.
         * Media feature tag used: g.3gpp.ps2cs-srvcc-orig-pre-alerting.

variables.name: MIDCALL_SRVCC_SUPPORT
variables.comment:
* SRVCC access transfer for calls in mid-call phase as per 3GPP 24.237. * and IR.64 Section 4.4. *

This means UE supports the MSC server assisted mid-call feature. * Media feature tag used: g.3gpp.mid-call.

variables.name: KEY_SRVCC_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of different SRVCC types supported as defined in 3GPP 24.237. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #BASIC_SRVCC_SUPPORT}, * {@link #ALERTING_SRVCC_SUPPORT}, * {@link #PREALERTING_SRVCC_SUPPORT}, * {@link #MIDCALL_SRVCC_SUPPORT} * *

Reference: IR.64, 3GPP 24.237, 3GPP 23.216

variables.name: KEY_RINGING_TIMER_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the ringing timer for Mobile terminated calls. * *

Ringing timer starts when the device sends SIP 180 Ringing in * response to a received SIP INVITE. If Ringing timer expires, * the device sends SIP 486 response.

variables.name: KEY_RINGBACK_TIMER_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the ringback timer for Mobile originated calls. * *

Ringback timer starts when the device receives SIP 180 Ringing * in response to its SIP INVITE. If Ringback timer expires, * the device sends SIP CANCEL.

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_RTP_INACTIVITY_TIMER_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the timeout value for RTP inactivity for audio media. *

On timer expiry, call will end. * See {@link #KEY_AUDIO_INACTIVITY_CALL_END_REASONS_INT_ARRAY} for more * details. *

Value of 0 means this timer is not enabled.

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_RTCP_INACTIVITY_TIMER_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the timeout value for RTCP inactivity for audio media. *

On timer expiry, call will end. * See {@link #KEY_AUDIO_INACTIVITY_CALL_END_REASONS_INT_ARRAY} for more * details. *

Value of 0 means this timer is not enabled.

variables.name: KEY_CONFERENCE_FACTORY_URI_STRING
variables.comment:
* Used to specify the conference factory URI. * *

If this is empty, then conference URI is generated from MCC/MNC as * specified in clause 13.10 of 3GPP 23.003.

variables.name: SESSION_REFRESH_METHOD_INVITE
variables.comment: * SIP INVITE is used for Session Refresh

variables.name: SESSION_REFRESH_METHOD_UPDATE_PREFERRED
variables.comment:
* Both SIP INVITE and UPDATE are used for session refresh. * *

SIP UPDATE will be used if UPDATE is in 'Allow' header. * If UPDATE is not in 'Allow' header, then INVITE will be used.

variables.name: KEY_SESSION_REFRESH_METHOD_INT
variables.comment:
* This is used to specify the method used for session refresh. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #SESSION_REFRESH_METHOD_INVITE}, * {@link #SESSION_REFRESH_METHOD_UPDATE_PREFERRED}

variables.name: KEY_OIP_SOURCE_FROM_HEADER_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the 'From' header field is used for determination of * the originating party identity in Originating Identification Presentation(OIP) * service. * *

If {@code true}: Indicates that the 'From' header field is used for * determination of the originating party identity in OIP. * {@code false} otherwise.

variables.name: KEY_MO_CALL_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the timer value for INVITE to the first 1xx response * (including 100 trying). If no response is received at timer expiry, * call is redialed over CS. * *

Reference: 24.173 Table L.1

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_INACTIVITY_CALL_END_REASONS_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of various reasons of media inactivity for which * voice/emergency call will end. * *

Possible values are, * {@link Ims#RTCP_INACTIVITY_ON_HOLD}, * {@link Ims#RTCP_INACTIVITY_ON_CONNECTED}, * {@link Ims#RTP_INACTIVITY_ON_CONNECTED} * {@link Ims#E911_RTCP_INACTIVITY_ON_CONNECTED}, * {@link Ims#E911_RTP_INACTIVITY_ON_CONNECTED}

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_AS_BANDWIDTH_KBPS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the AS (Application Specific) SDP modifier for audio media. * *

This value is expressed in kilobits per second. * Reference: RFC 3556 Section 2.

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_RS_BANDWIDTH_BPS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the RS SDP modifier for audio media. This indicates the RTCP * bandwidth allocated to active data senders for audio media. * *

This value is expressed in bits per second. * Reference: RFC 3556 Section 2.

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_RR_BANDWIDTH_BPS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the RR SDP modifier for audio media. This indicates the RTCP * bandwidth allocated to receivers for audio media. * *

This value is expressed in bits per second. * Reference: RFC 3556 Section 2.

variables.name: KEY_AUDIO_CODEC_CAPABILITY_PAYLOAD_TYPES_BUNDLE
variables.comment:
* Specifies the Audio Codec capability. This contains a list of payload types * representing different audio codec instances. * *

The priority of the codecs is EVS, AMRWB, AMRNB, DTMF WB, DTMF NB * from highest to lowest. In each individual codec, the priority is determined * by the order of the payload types from highest to lowest. * *

Possible keys in this bundle are, *

    *
  • {@link #KEY_EVS_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_DTMFWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_DTMFNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
*

To specify payload descriptions for each of the audio payload types, see *

    *
  • {@link #KEY_EVS_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE}
    • *

variables.name: KEY_EVS_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of integers representing the different payload types * in EVS codec in priority order from highest to lowest. *

Payload type is an integer in dynamic payload type range 96-127 * as per RFC RFC 3551 Section 6.

variables.name: KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of integers representing the different payload types * in AMR-WB codec in priority order from highest to lowest. *

Payload type is an integer in dynamic payload type range 96-127 * as per RFC RFC 3551 Section 6.

variables.name: KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of integers representing the different payload types * in AMR-NB codec in priority order from highest to lowest. *

Payload type is an integer in dynamic payload type range 96-127 * as per RFC RFC 3551 Section 6.

variables.name: KEY_DTMFWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of integers representing the different payload types * in DTMF WB codec in priority order from highest to lowest. *

Payload type is an integer in dynamic payload type range 96-127 * as per RFC RFC 3551 Section 6.

variables.name: KEY_DTMFNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of integers representing the different payload types * in DTMF NB codec in priority order from highest to lowest. *

Payload type is an integer in dynamic payload type range 96-127 * as per RFC RFC 3551 Section 6.

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_RTP_PACKET_LOSS_RATE_THRESHOLD_INT
variables.comment:
* This indicates the threshold for RTP packet loss rate in percentage. If measured packet
         * loss rate crosses this, a callback with {@link MediaQualityStatus} will be invoked to
         * listeners.
         * See {@link android.telephony.TelephonyCallback.MediaQualityStatusChangedListener}
         *
         * <p/>
         * Valid threshold range : 0 ~ 100
         *
         * @hide

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_RTP_JITTER_THRESHOLD_MILLIS_INT
variables.comment:
* This indicates the threshold for RTP jitter value in milliseconds (RFC3550). If measured
         * jitter value crosses this, a callback with {@link MediaQualityStatus} will be invoked
         * to listeners.
         * See {@link android.telephony.TelephonyCallback.MediaQualityStatusChangedListener}
         *
         * <p/>
         * Valid threshold range : 0 ~ 10000
         *
         * @hide

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_RTP_INACTIVITY_TIME_THRESHOLD_MILLIS_LONG
variables.comment:
* This indicates the threshold for RTP inactivity time in milliseconds. If measured
         * inactivity timer crosses this, a callback with {@link MediaQualityStatus} will be invoked
         * to listeners.
         * See {@link android.telephony.TelephonyCallback.MediaQualityStatusChangedListener}
         *
         * <p/>
         * Valid threshold range : 0 ~ 60000
         *
         * @hide

variables.name: BANDWIDTH_EFFICIENT
variables.comment: AMR NB/WB Payload format is bandwidth-efficient.

variables.name: OCTET_ALIGNED
variables.comment: AMR NB/WB Payload format is octet-aligned.

variables.name: KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_PAYLOAD_FORMAT_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the payload format of the AMR-NB/AMR-WB codec. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #BANDWIDTH_EFFICIENT}, * {@link #OCTET_ALIGNED} *

If value is not specified, payload format is * {@link #BANDWIDTH_EFFICIENT}. * *

Reference: RFC 4867 Section 8.1.

variables.name: KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODESET_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Restricts the active mode set to a subset of all modes in the codec. * *

This attribute is optional. If value is set, then session mode * set is restricted to the modes specified in this list. If this value * is not specified, then all available modes in the codec are allowed. * This attribute is applicable for AMR-WB, AMR-NB, * and EVS codec (operating in AMR-WB IO Mode). * *

Possible values are subset of, * [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8] - AMRWB with the modes representing nine speech codec modes * with bit rates of 6.6, 8.85, 12.65, 14.25, 15.85, 18.25, 19.85, 23.05, 23.85 kbps. * [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7] - AMRNB with the modes representing eight speech codec modes * with bit rates of 4.75, 5.15, 5.90, 6.70, 7.40, 7.95, 10.2, 12.2 kbps. * *

If value is not specified, then it means device supports all * modes in the codec but not included in SDP. * *

Reference: RFC 4867 Section 8.1, 3GPP 26.445 A.3.1

variables.name: KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE
variables.comment:
* Specifies the codec attributes of different payload types in * the AMR NarrowBand (AMR-NB) codec. * *

The keys in this bundle are payload types specified * in {@link #KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}. * *

Codec attributes allowed as part of AMR-NB codec bundle are, *

    *
  • {@link #KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_PAYLOAD_FORMAT_INT}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODESET_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
* *

If this bundle is not configured and AMRNB payload type is added * in {@link #KEY_AMRNB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}, then default * values as in the individual codec attribute to be used * for that payload type.

variables.name: KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE
variables.comment:
* Specifies the codec attributes of different payload types in * the AMR WideBand (AMR-WB) codec. * *

The keys in this bundle are payload types specified * in {@link #KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}. * *

Codec attributes allowed as part of AMR-NB codec bundle are, *

    *
  • {@link #KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_PAYLOAD_FORMAT_INT}
    • *
  • {@link #KEY_AMR_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODESET_INT_ARRAY}
    • *
* *

If this bundle is not configured and AMRWB payload type is added * in {@link #KEY_AMRWB_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}, then default * values as in the individual codec attribute to be used * for that payload type.

variables.name: EVS_OPERATIONAL_MODE_PRIMARY
variables.comment: Indicates the EVS primary mode. 3GPP 26.445 Section 3.1

variables.name: EVS_OPERATIONAL_MODE_AMRWB_IO
variables.comment: Indicates the EVS AMR-WB IO mode. 3GPP 26.445 Section 3.1

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODE_SWITCH_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies if the EVS mode used is EVS primary mode * or EVS AMR-WB IO mode. * *

Possible values are, * {@link #EVS_OPERATIONAL_MODE_PRIMARY}, * {@link #EVS_OPERATIONAL_MODE_AMRWB_IO} * *

If this is not present, then {@link #EVS_OPERATIONAL_MODE_PRIMARY} is used. *

Reference: 3GPP 26.445 Section 3.1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is Narrow Band (NB).
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is Wide Band (WB).
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_SWB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is Super WideBand (SWB).
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_FB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is Full Band (FB).
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is in the range NB,WB.
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB_SWB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is in the range NB,WB,SWB.
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB_SWB_FB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is in the range NB,WB,SWB,FB.
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB_SWB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is in the range WB,SWB.
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB_SWB_FB
variables.comment:
* EVS encoded Bandwidth is in the range WB,SWB,FB.
         * Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_BANDWIDTH_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the EVS codec encoding bandwidth options. * * Possible values are, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_SWB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_FB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB_SWB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB_SWB_FB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB_SWB}, * {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_WB_SWB_FB} * * If this key is not specified, then the behavior is same as * value {@link #EVS_ENCODED_BW_TYPE_NB_WB_SWB} * *

Reference: 3GPP 26.441 Table 1.

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_5_9_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 5.9 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_7_2_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 7.2 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_8_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 8.0 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_9_6_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 9.6 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_13_2_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 13.2 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_16_4_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 16.4 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_24_4_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 24.4 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_32_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 32.0 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_48_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 48.0 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_64_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 64.0 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_96_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 96.0 kbps

variables.name: EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_128_0_KBPS
variables.comment: EVS primary mode with bitrate 128.0 kbps

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_BITRATE_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Specifies the range of source codec bit-rate for EVS Primary mode * in the session. This is expressed in kilobits per second and * applicable for both the send and the receive directions. * *

The range is specified as integer aray of size 2, * represented as [low, high], where low <= high * *

Possible values for low and high are, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_5_9_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_7_2_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_8_0_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_9_6_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_13_2_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_16_4_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_24_4_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_32_0_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_48_0_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_64_0_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_96_0_KBPS}, * {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_128_0_KBPS} * * If this key is not specified, then the behavior is same as * value {@link #EVS_PRIMARY_MODE_BITRATE_24_4_KBPS} * *

Reference: 3GPP 26.445 Section A.3.1

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_CH_AW_RECV_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the Channel aware mode (ch-aw-recv) for the receive direction. * This is applicable for EVS codec. * *

Permissible values are -1, 0, 2, 3, 5, and 7. * If this key is not specified, then the behavior is same as value 0 * (channel aware mode disabled). *

If this key is configured, then device is expected to send * this parameter in the SDP offer. * *

Reference: 3GPP TS 26.445 section 4.4.5, 3GPP 26.445 Section A.3.1

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_HF_ONLY_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies whether to limit the session to header-full format. * This applies to both directions in the session. This attribute * is applicable for EVS codec. * *

Permissible values are 0, 1 * If hf-only is 1, only Header-Full format is used and hf-only is * included in the SDP. *

If hf-only is 0, both Compact and Header-Full formats are used * and hf-only is included in the SDP. *

If this key is not present, then both Compact * and Header-Full formats are used and hf-only is not included in * the SDP. *

If this key is configured, then device is expected to send * this parameter in the SDP offer if operator required it. * *

Reference: 3GPP 26.445 Section A.3.1.

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_DTX_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Specifies whether DTX (Discontinuous transmission) is enabled * or not. This applies to both directions in the session. * This attribute is applicable for EVS codec and can be used * in both EVS Primary mode and EVS AMR-WB IO mode. * *

If {@code true}: Indicates DTX is enabled. * If {@code false}: Indicates DTX is disabled. * *

If this is not present, then default value of {@code true} * will apply. *

Reference: 3GPP TS 26.445 Section A.3.1.

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_DTX_RECV_BOOL
variables.comment:
* This is used if further restriction is required on DTX in the * receive direction. This attribute is applicable for EVS codec * and can be used in both EVS Primary mode and EVS AMR-WB IO mode. * *

If this value is true or not present, then DTX setting is * dependent on {@link #KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_DTX_BOOL}. * *

If this is not present, then default value of {@code true} * will apply. * *

Reference: 3GPP TS 26.445 Section A.3.1.

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_CHANNELS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the number of audio channels. * If this is not present, then default value of 1 will apply. * *

Reference: RFC 3551

variables.name: KEY_EVS_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_CMR_INT
variables.comment:
* Indicates whether the Codec Mode Request (CMR) is supported * for the session. * This attribute is applicable for EVS codec in Primary Mode only. * *

Possible values are -1, 0, 1. If this key is not present, * then behavior as per value 0 is applicable. * *

Reference: 3GPP 26.445 Section A.3.1, 3GPP 26.114 Table 6.2a

variables.name: KEY_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODE_CHANGE_PERIOD_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the number of frame-blocks. This indicates the frame-block period * at which codec mode changes are allowed for the sender. This attribute is * applicable for EVS codec in AMR-WB IO mode and AMR-WB. * *

Possible values are 1, 2. * If the key is not present, behavior as per value 1 is applicable and this * parameter is not included in SDP. * *

Reference: RFC 4867 Section 8.1.

variables.name: KEY_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODE_CHANGE_CAPABILITY_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies if the client is capable to transmit with a restricted mode * change period. This attribute is applicable for EVS codec in * AMR-WB IO mode and AMR-WB. * *

Possible values are 1, 2. If this key is not present, * then behavior as per value 1 is applicable and this * parameter is not included in SDP. * *

Reference: RFC 4867 Section 8.1.

variables.name: KEY_CODEC_ATTRIBUTE_MODE_CHANGE_NEIGHBOR_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the allowed mode changes for the sender in the active mode set. * This attribute is applicable for EVS codec in AMR-WB IO mode * and AMR-WB. * *

Possible values are 0, 1. If value is 1, then the sender should only * perform mode changes to the neighboring modes in the active codec mode set. * If value is 0, then mode changes between any two modes * in the active codec mode set is allowed. * If the key is not present, behavior as per value 0 is applicable and this * parameter is not included in SDP. * *

Reference: RFC 4867 Section 8.1.

variables.name: KEY_EVS_PAYLOAD_DESCRIPTION_BUNDLE
variables.comment:
* Specifies the codec attributes of different payload types in * the EVS codec. * *

The keys in this bundle are payload types specified * in {@link #KEY_EVS_PAYLOAD_TYPE_INT_ARRAY}. * *

Codec attributes allowed as part of EVS codec are, *
